      <PointerOffset/>
      <JapaneseText>『絵、見る』でやめときゃ
マルタのモデル姿拝めたかもしれねぇのに</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>If Emil had just stopped "looking at the picture",
he might have been able to see Marta as a model.</EnglishText>
      <Notes>絵、見る is e, mi ru which = Emiru. I'll work on this later.</Notes>
      <SpeakerId>3</SpeakerId>
      <Id>1</Id>
      <Status>Problematic</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset/>
      <JapaneseText>マルタは……丸太で……えーと</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>Marta is... a log... Ummm...</EnglishText>
      <Notes>丸太 = logs but is pronounced Maruta. Marta's katakana is Maruta. I'll work on this later.</Notes>
      <SpeakerId>2</SpeakerId>
      <Id>2</Id>
      <Status>Problematic</Status>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <PointerOffset/>
      <JapaneseText>なんだよ、考えてる途中だったのかよ</JapaneseText>
      <EnglishText>What the heck?
You were thinking that up this whole time?</EnglishText>
